data.meta_description: Nevada Reports 1967 (83 Nev.).pdf - Free ebook download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read book online for free. The Supreme Court of Nevada affirmed the denial of a writ of habeas corpus, finding that the evidence presented at the preliminary examination was sufficient to warrant binding the defendant over for trial on charges of lewdness with a child under 14. Specifically, the child victim testified that the defendant touched her private parts and the defendant admitted inviting the child into his home and accidentally touching her private parts while tying his shoe. This evidence was sufficient to support a reasonable inference that the defendant committed the offense.
